# Cloudflare Pages routing rules.
#
# Pages cannot proxy /api/* to an external host (api.mediterian-heatwaves.com)
# via _redirects status=200 — that only works for same-origin destinations.
# The frontend instead hits the API subdomain directly using VITE_API_BASE
# baked in at build time, with CORS allow-listed on the backend.

# SPA fallback — every unknown path serves index.html so client-side
# routing (e.g. /about) keeps working on direct loads + reloads.
/*  /index.html  200
